snippet.textDisplay: If EA does this nickel and dime crap with Sims 5 I will be done with this series for good. People have been saying it but Sims needs competition. Its sat at the top unchallenged for too long. For one, the fans have been supporting Sims 4 for 6 years! Sims 1 had 3 years of support, 2 had 4 years and 3 had 4. At this point it feels like a lazy way to greedily milk Sims 4 as for as much as possible until EA has to release 5 again and sadly repeat this process. Expansion packs made sense back in 03' because we didn't have good internet to download stuff but now we don't get staple features in base Sims games anymore because EA has hardwired its customers to think packs are normal. We had to wait 5 years for magic!!! The DLC list and their prices for Sims 4 is insane and tbh shameful. Asking EA and in turn whichever developers they hire to change is next to impossible but I would at least like to believe they have some kind of integrity left.

Expansion packs made sense back in 03' because we didn't have good internet to download stuff but now we don't get staple features in base Sims games anymore because EA has hardwired its customers to think packs are normal.
